# aretheyup Project Description

aretheyup is a real-time outage detector for internet services

The app decides whether a service is `Operational` or `Issues Detected` using:

- crowdsourced user reports in a rolling 30 minute window
- optional probe results when probe data is available
- historical baselines by hour of week to avoid false positives

The product is server-rendered and HTMX-driven

- home page shows a live list of services
- service page shows one live service card
- both pages auto-refresh on a timer

Core product goals:

- fast and simple status checks for end users
- minimal client-side complexity
- graceful behavior during cold start and partial data availability

Non-goals right now:

- websocket-first architecture
- heavy SPA client logic
- hard dependency on probe infrastructure
